article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 81, Elon 77
article.story: ELON, N.C. (AP) -- Gerald Robinson had 25 points and 10 rebounds to lead Tennessee-Martin past Elon 81-77 on Saturday night. Lester Hudson scored 21 points and Marquis Weddle added 20 for the Skyhawks (16-14), who shot 40 percent and forced 15 turnovers in extending their winning streak to six. Montell Watson had 20 points and Brett James added 18 for Elon (11-17), which has lost two of three since winning three straight earlier this month. Adam Constantine contributed 15 rebounds and Ola Atoyebi scored 11 points for the Phoenix.
